('James Ransby', 'James', 'Ransby', 'General Manager', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jamesransby', 'jamesransby', $${"about": "I am a versatile, multi-lingual Hospitality Executive with a 20-year career spanning luxury resort management, entrepreneurship, and Information Technology. My approach combines high-touch service standards with a data-driven focus on operational efficiency and financial performance.\n\n\n\nIn my current role as General Manager of a 65-room luxury boutique resort in Koh Samui, Thailand, I spearheaded a strategic turnaround that delivered substantial increases in both total revenue and GOP within my first year. This success was built on a foundation of entrepreneurial stewardship; having spent seven years as a restaurateur and business owner, I view every P&L with an owner’s mindset, prioritising long-term asset value and meticulous cost control.\n\n\n\nMy background includes over eight years of hotel management experience, having served as General Manager, Resort Manager, Operations Manager, Executive Assistant Manager, and Sales & Marketing Manager.\n\n\n\nMy Core Expertise Includes:\n\n- Strategic Turnarounds & Growth: Proven ability to rapidly scale revenue and profitability in competitive markets.\n\n- Project Leadership: Extensive experience leading pre-openings, soft openings, and phased renovations in Thailand; including the successful opening of a 104-capacity function hall in the UK.\n\n- Commercial & Sales Strategy: Expertise in B2B/B2C channels, media representation, digital marketing, and the production of web marketing materials.\n\n- Operational Depth: Comprehensive management of 5-star facilities, including multi-outlet F&B, luxury spas, wellness/yoga facilities, fitness centers, and co-working spaces.\n\n- Linguistic & Technical Edge: Native English speaker, fluent in Thai, with business French and conversational German. I also bring six years of experience in Information Systems and software project management, providing a un