nd-in-command, under direct request from the team of partners following my successful earlier term at the resort.\n\nOverseeing daily operations in Front Office, Housekeeping, Engineering, F&B (restaurant service and kitchen teams), Spa, Accounting and Human Resources.", "experiences/7/jobEndedOn": "9-2013", "experiences/7/jobStartedOn": "10-2012", "experiences/7/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/7/title": "Operations Manager", "experiences/8/companyName": "Blue Lagoon Hotel & Chaweng Beachcomber", "experiences/8/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/8/jobDescription": "Management for hotel operations and administration for 2 sister hotels, a 74-room 4-star hotel and a 63-room 3-star hotel.\n\nResponsible for overseeing all hotel operations - Front Office, Housekeeping, Engineering, F&B (service, and kitchen) - and working closely with the Human Resources and Accounting teams).\n\nI also focused on re-opening many sales channels which had previously ceased working with these hotels; and occupancy dramatically increased accordingly. The Web sites for the hotels were also greatly improved.\n\nI also oversaw major renovations in both hotels (as they were both quite dated). Under my stewardship, the operational room inventory at Chaweng Beachcomber increased from 21 rooms to 62, and the Blue Lagoon experienced a complete renovation of the lobby area.\n\nI was Acting GM for much of my time here.", "experiences/8/jobEndedOn": "8-2012", "experiences/8/jobLocation": "Chaweng, Koh Samui", "experiences/8/jobStartedOn": "10-2011", "experiences/8/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/8/title": "Executive Assistant Manager", "experiences/9/companyName": "Panorama Patong", "experiences/9/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/9/jobDescription": "A condominium building had stalled due to the death of the original developer, and I was employed by the Legal Administrator to lead the marketing and pre- & post-sales activity for a condominium building during construct